  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0baf \u0b86\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0ba4\u0bbf : \u0b85\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd - \u0b9c\u0bc7.\u0bb5\u0bbf.\u0baa\u0bbf.",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Govt conspiracy against today's protest: Be cautious - JVP",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "The government is plotting to incite violence and stifle mass protests on Saturday.",
        "This conspiracy of the government should not be allowed to succeed. Therefore, General Secretary of People's Liberation Front (JVP) Dilvin Silva said that everyone is requested to be very careful during the demonstration.",
        "JVP in Bhattaramulla He stated this at a press conference held at the headquarters on Friday (08) while further stating,",
        "Even though it has been two months since the new government was formed, there has been no benefit to the people.",
        "On the contrary, schools, government services, hospitals are all paralyzed. No one knows the date of arrival of the fuel ship.",
        "People are struggling between life and death. The government that created such a situation should be kicked out.",
        "Despite the crisis people are facing, President Gotabaya Rajapaksa and Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe are smiling.",
        "They should be made to step down and hand over to those who can build the country. Empty face protestors J.V.P. Discussed with President Anurakumara Dissanayake and others.",
        "During the demonstration on the 9th (today's demonstration) J.V.P. He assured full cooperation.",
        "Everyone must come together to make this demonstration a success. The government is plotting to incite violence and quell the protests.",
        "The democratic right to protest is enshrined in the Constitution. We inform the government that this cannot be blocked by conspiracy.",
        "The protestors must not in any way give way to the success of the government's conspiracy to incite violence.",
        "What we are going to do is the democratic struggle. We will definitely win in this. We fully believe that success lies with people.",
        "Mahinda Rajapaksa and Bashil Rajapaksa resigned due to popular protests. Similarly, the current government should also be forced to resign.",
        "The government has no right to attack unarmed demonstrators. So the security forces should also ensure their safety from the people's side, he said."
      ],
